      "content": "RICE is a good first-aid measure for a minor sprain, but your ankle sounds quite serious, so you should be cautious. For immediate relief, apply ice packs for 15-20 minutes every few hours, and elevate your foot above your heart. While you can try to manage it with RICE, if you can't bear weight, you should definitely consider getting a proper diagnosis from a medical professional, like a clinic or urgent care, to rule out anything more serious.",
