      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a bad sprain, you need to be a little more thorough than just resting, but if you're determined to try the home remedy route, I can tell you to stick to the RICE protocol strictly. Keep that elevation high, use the ibuprofen as directed, and keep icing it religiously for the next four days. If you can move your toes, that's a good sign, but if the pain is still severe after 48 hours, you'll know it's time to get a professional opinion, no excuses!",
